Incident.Summary: MOTOR VEHICLE COLLISION - PROPERTY DAMAGE / FIREARM DISCHARGE

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: CASE NUMBER: 23-MSP-032484 INVESTIGATING TROOPER: Trooper First Class M. Mowbray #7119 NATURE OF CALL: Firearm Discharge, Motor Vehicle Collision SCENE PROCESSING: Scene processing was conducted with the following results; margin-left:8px">Four (4) photographs of scene/evidence uploaded to DeltaPlus and VeriPic INCIDENT FOOTAGE: LABLED 23-MSP-032484 ON AXON EVIDENCE INCIDENT CAPTURED WITH MOBILE VIDEO RECORDER (MVR): I-12 Mobile Video Recorder (Outward Facing): partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline">https://mdsp.evidence.com/axon/evidence?evidence_id=c824c626a78f4addaae0449a6fcfd470partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1 INCIDENT CAPTURED BY BODY WORN CAMERA (BWC) TFC Mowbray #7119 Body Worn Camera): partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline">https://mdsp.evidence.com/axon/evidence?evidence_id=ce137251c70c4e248e3c6d1da02951c5partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1 NARRATIVE: On September 15, 2023, at approximately 2242 hours I, Trooper First Class M. Mowbray #7119 of the Maryland State Police Easton Barrack, was dispatched to the intersection of Maryland Route 307 and Palmer Mill Road, Hurlock, Dorchester County, Maryland regarding a motor vehicle collision. Upon my arrival I made contact with personnel from the Hurlock Volunteer Fire Company that advised that the collision involved one vehicle and all occupants were uninjured. I was also advised that the vehicle had struck a deer, which was still alive within the ditch suffering from a broken left rear leg. I retrieved my personally owned Remington 870 12-gauge shotgun from the secured gun safe within my Maryland State Police patrol vehicle I-12 and located the deer within the ditch to assess its injuries. After assessing the injuries to the deer, and determining that they were non-recoverable, in accordance with MSP OPS 10.02, I discharged one (1) round of 00 buckshot toward the deer, striking it behind its right shoulder incapacitating the animal to relieve it from its suffering. I then made contact with the operator of the white 2019 Mitsubishi Outlander bearing Maryland registration 2EP4167; identified as LaMiaya Sharnai Camper (DOB: 05/07/1993) [hereinafter identified as Camper]. Camper advised she was traveling northbound on Maryland Route 307 near Palmer Mill Road when a deer entered the roadway from the left, running directly into her path. Camper stated that she struck the deer as it crossed in front of her. Camper and her three juvenile children were uninjured. A preliminary investigation corroborated Campers statement. Camper was provided all appropriate documents at the scene. All events occurred in Dorchester County.
